{"questionId":"9273","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The functions <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"f\">\n  <mi>f</mi>\n</math></span> and <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"g\">\n  <mi>g</mi>\n</math></span> are defined such that&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"f\\left( x \\right) = \\frac{{x + 3}}{4}\">\n  <mi>f</mi>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mi>x</mi>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mi>x</mi>\n      <mo>+</mo>\n      <mn>3</mn>\n    </mrow>\n    <mn>4</mn>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span> and&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"g\\left( x \\right) = 8x + 5\">\n  <mi>g</mi>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mi>x</mi>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>8</mn>\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mn>5</mn>\n</math></span>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Given that <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{\\left( {g \\circ f} \\right)^{ - 1}}\\left( a \\right) = 4\">\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mrow>\n        <mo>(</mo>\n        <mrow>\n          <mi>g</mi>\n          <mo>∘</mo>\n          <mi>f</mi>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo>)</mo>\n      </mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <mo>−</mo>\n        <mn>1</mn>\n      </mrow>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mi>a</mi>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>4</mn>\n</math></span>, find the value of <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"a\">\n  <mi>a</mi>\n</math></span>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>attempt to substitute 4 (seen anywhere)&nbsp;<em><strong> &nbsp; &nbsp;(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>correct equation&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"a = 2 \\times 4 + 11\">\n  <mi>a</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>2</mn>\n  <mo>×</mo>\n  <mn>4</mn>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mn>11</mn>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>&nbsp;&nbsp;(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"a\">\n  <mi>a</mi>\n</math></span> = 19&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong>[3 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"9273","referenceCode":"SPM.1.SL.TZ0.5b","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Given that ( g ∘ f ) − 1 ( a ) = 4 , find the value of a .","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"b","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 3]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 2—Functions","Topic 2—Functions","SL 2.5—Composite functions, identity, finding inverse"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}